    "description": "Katakura & Co-op Agri Corporation engages in the fertilizer, cosmetic, chemical, feed, real estate, and other businesses in Japan and internationally. The company offers a range of agricultural materials, including chemical fertilizers and compound fertilizers, raising seedling soil, liquid, mixed, soil making, simple, molded mixed, pesticide, paste, simple, and silica fertilizers, as well as microbial material and seedling culture soil. It also supplies ammonia, industrial phosphoric acid, phosphoric acid for food and fertilizers, and sulfuric acid, as well as tank rental business. In addition, the company provides calcium carbonate for feed additives for a wide range of applications, such as poultry farming, pig farming, dairy cattle, beef cattle, and other marine products; manufactures, sells, and designs and develops synthetic clay minerals; provides physicochemical analysis, biologic analysis, quality analysis of agricultural products and crop cultivation tests, etc. Further, it develops, manufactures, and sells cosmetic raw materials for skin care, hair care, and make-up; and management, operation, and sale of real estate properties. The company was founded in 1920 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
